---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | Orboro.net" description="Privacy policy for Orboro.net">
  <section>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: July 2026</p>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      This site (Orboro.net) is a personal site operated by JD. It does not sell, share,
      or monetise any personal data. This policy explains what limited information is collected
      and why.
    </p>

    <h2>Information Collected</h2>
    <h3>Server logs</h3>
    <p>
      Like most web servers, this site may log standard request metadata — including IP address,
      browser user-agent, referring URL, and the page requested. These logs are used solely for
      diagnosing errors and understanding traffic patterns. They are not linked to any personal
      identity and are retained for a short period before being discarded.
    </p>

    <h3>Analytics</h3>
    <p>
      This site uses Google Analytics to understand how visitors use it — pages viewed, approximate
      location, device/browser type, and referring pages. Google Analytics sets cookies and stores an
      identifier in your browser to do this. This data is aggregated and is not linked to your name,
      email, or any account. No advertising pixels are used, and no data is sold or shared with
      advertisers.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can opt out of Google Analytics tracking using
      <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Google's browser opt-out add-on
      </a>, or with any browser extension that blocks third-party analytics scripts.
    </p>

    <h3>Third-party links</h3>
    <p>
      This site contains links to external platforms (Reddit, Discord, the official Path of Exile site). Once
      you leave this site, this privacy policy no longer applies. Please review the privacy
      practices of those platforms directly.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Storage</h2>
    <p>
      The site is hosted on Cloudflare's infrastructure. Cloudflare's own
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Privacy Policy
      </a>
      governs any data processed at the network layer. Analytics data described above is processed by
      Google in accordance with
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Google's Privacy Policy
      </a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Your Rights</h2>
    <p>
      Beyond the aggregated analytics data and transient server logs described above, no personal
      data is collected, so there is little to access, correct, or delete. If you have a concern,
      you can reach out via the contact details on the platform profiles listed on the homepage.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      This policy may be updated occasionally. The "last updated" date at the top of the page
      will reflect any changes.
    </p>

    <hr />
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  section {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .updated {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: -0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  h3 {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
</style>
